class Solution {
    public int maximumLengthSubstring(String s) {
        int[] freq = new int[26];
        int left = 0, max = 0;
        for (int right = 0; right < s.length(); right++) {
            int c = s.charAt(right) - 'a';
            freq[c]++;
            while (freq[c] > 2) {
                freq[s.charAt(left++) - 'a']--;
            }
            max = Math.max(max, right - left + 1);
        }
        return max;
    }
}
```
efficiency: HIGH
time complexity: O(n)
space complexity: O(1)
energy implications: LOW
explanation: Sliding-window technique keeps a frequency array of size 26. Expand the window until any character exceeds two occurrences, then shrink from the left until valid again. Single pass gives linear time and constant space.

